-- Sprint Tentatively Sets June 12 for SoftBank Shareholder Vote
-- B y   C r a y t o n   H a r r i s o n
-- 2013-04-26T21:45:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-04-26/sprint-tentatively-sets-june-12-for-softbank-shareholder-vote.html
Sprint Nextel Corp. (S)  said it
tentatively set June 12 as the date for a shareholder vote on
 SoftBank Corp. (9984) ’s takeover offer.  The date is pending approval of the Securities and Exchange
Commission’s approval of Sprint’s proxy filing,  Scott Sloat , a
Sprint spokesman, said in an e-mail. Reuters reported the date
earlier today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Crayton Harrison at 
 tharrison5@bloomberg.net  